Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[On top of eco-toxicological factors, which seem to be the priority
candidates for the scenario as described, infectious diseases --
though rather unlikely -- deserve to be excluded by lab
investigations. - Mod.AS]

[Hydrogen sulphide is capable of dissipating, even after it has caused
death. Consequently, not finding rotten seaweed in the stomach does
not mean the animal did not inhale sufficient quantities of the gas to
die from it. - Mod.TG]

[The interactive HealthMap/ProMED map for Brittany is available at:
http://healthmap.org/r/00G2 - CopyEd.EJP]
